   READER'S DIGEST ASSOCIATION Inc.(Pleasantville, N.Y.) --
Anthony W. Ruggiero was elected vice president and chief
financial officer and Melvin R. Laird was elected to the
board of this publisher and direct marketer. Mr. Ruggiero, 49
years old, succeeds Vernon Thomas, who stepped down earlier
for health reasons. Mr. Laird, 67, fills a vacancy created
when Richard F. McLoughlin retired as president. Mr. Laird is
Reader's Digest's senior vice president and counselor for
national and international affairs.
